title: Uncontrolled scrolling of tab bar
content: Firefox version 142.01. After the update I find that Firefox opens normally with tabs visible as normal. When I use the > button to scroll to tabs not visible, the tabs scroll as normal but as soon as I release the mouse button they immediately and rapidly scroll back to the original position. This means I am unable to access many of my tabs. I have searched for information on this but have not been able to find anything specific. I have cleared cookies etc., refreshed Firefox, used a different mouse all to no avail. Another issue is that when trying to select which topic best describes my problem, the pop up only flashes on the screen and when it does stay on, it vanishes again when I try to select an issue. I managed to select the one shown but it was the only one I could access. I don't know what else to do. Any help will be gratefully received. Thanks. Owen

title: Problemas con reproduccion de streaming en vivo en youtube y miniaturas de youtube
content:
Hola, el problema es el siguiente: Al agrandar la pantalla a pantalla completa en videos en vivo, o sea streaming en vivo en youtube, de repente mi computadora empieza a consumir muchos recursos y el video para de reproducirse, y no responda al mouse, solo al teclado. Cabe aclarar que esto solo empezo a pasar hace algunos dias, antes podia reproducirlos sin ningun problema, y que esto solo sucede con los streaming en vivo, ademas de eso en otros navegadores esto no sucede, pero me gustaria poder seguir usando mozilla y no verme obligado a cambiar de navegador

Tambien otro problema menor pero molesto es que a veces al ingresar a youtube las miniaturas se ven muy grandes y a veces mas pequeñas, esto sucede de manera al azar, el zoom de la pantalla es siempre el mismo, y las miniaturas cambias de manera random de tamaño al ingresar a youtube. Muchas gracias!

title: Extra steps to check if a site is safe in Firefox
content: I’ve been using Firefox as my main browser for a while and I really like the built-in protections against phishing and tracking. Still, I sometimes worry about clicking on unfamiliar links, especially when they come from emails or social media. To be extra safe, I started running new sites through a Website checker before opening them in Firefox. One I’ve found useful is review, since it gives a quick trust score and lets me know if the site has been reported as suspicious. I’m just curious, do other Firefox users here take extra steps like this, or do you just rely on the browser’s built-in protections?
